# ENVIRONMENT MANAGEMENT

- Use .env files for local development (not committed to git)
- Document required environment variables in README
- Separate configurations for development, testing, and production
- Use python-dotenv for environment variable loading
- Implement configuration validation on startup

# CONFIGURATION MANAGEMENT

- Use environment variables for config
- Separate configuration from code
- Use YAML/JSON for complex settings
- Implement proper defaults for optional settings
- Document all configuration options

## Security Considerations
- Never hardcode credentials or secrets
- Use secure storage for sensitive configuration
- Implement proper access controls for configuration
- Rotate secrets regularly
- Log configuration changes 